  "prompt": "To which class cin and cout belongs?",
  "response": "In C++, `cin` and `cout` are objects that are part of the standard input-output library. They belong to the `std` namespace and are instances of the `std::istream` and `std::ostream` classes, respectively.\n\n- `cin` is an instance of `std::istream`, which is used for input operations.\n- `cout` is an instance of `std::ostream`, used for output operations.\n\nThese objects are defined in the `<iostream>` header file. You typically use these objects to read from standard input (usually the keyboard) and to write to standard output (usually the console).",
